# Per-Object Execution Card

**Load this ONCE at batch start. Never unload it. Load full phase rules on-demand per step.**

## Pipeline (standard path)

```
 #  Phase              Do what                                        Rule file            Gate
 1  Structure          Read SSDT DDL → columns, types, indexes        01-structure         HARD
 2  Sample + ETL       SELECT TOP 10 + row count + ETL source chain   02-live-data         HARD ← IMMEDIATE gate
 3  Distribution       Value counts, NULLs, enums                     03-distribution      SOFT
 4  Lookup             Resolve *ID → Dim/Dict (repo first, then MCP)  04-lookup            SOFT
 5  JOINs              Grep SPs/views for JOIN patterns               05-join-analysis     SOFT
 6  Business Logic     Column groups, hierarchies, flags              06-business-logic    SOFT
 7  View Deps          Which views reference this table?              07-view-dependency   SOFT
 8  SP Scan            Find writer/reader SPs (consume P2 results!)   08-procedure-scan    HARD
 9  SP Logic           Read top SPs deeply → source-to-target map     09-procedure-logic   HARD ← feeds lineage
 9B ETL Orchestration  Refresh schedule, dependencies                 09b-etl-orch         SOFT
10  Atlassian          Search Jira/Confluence for business context     10-atlassian         SOFT
10.5 Upstream Wiki     Generic Pipeline → production source → read    13-prod-lineage §1-3 HARD*
13  Column Lineage     Write .lineage.md (BEFORE doc!)                13-prod-lineage §2-6 HARD ← new position
11  Generate Doc       Read .lineage.md → write .md + .review-needed  11-generate-doc      HARD
12  Cross-Enrich       Pre-Read is embedded in P11; batch pass later  12-cross-enrich      —
```

*HARD when Phase 2 found a known source (staging/ext/migration). SOFT only if source genuinely unknown.

## Simple Dictionary Fast-Path

**Criteria**: ≤10 columns, no computed columns, single-source from SP_Dictionaries.

```
 1 → 2 → 8 → 4 → 10.5 → 11 → 13
```

Skip: P3 (trivial dist), P5 (no JOINs), P6 (no logic), P7 (no views), P9B (no orchestration), P10 (low value).
P9 runs only if SP_Dictionaries has non-trivial transforms (column renames, CASE, hardcoded values).

## Phase Gate Checklist (emit before Phase 11)

```
PHASE GATE CHECK — {ObjectName}:
  [x] P1 DDL   [x] P2 Sample   [x] P3 Dist   [x] P4 Lookup
  [x] P5 JOIN  [x] P6 BizLogic [x] P7 Views  [x] P8 SP-scan
  [x] P9 SP-logic [x] P9B ETL  [x] P10 Jira  [x] P10.5 Upstream
  → Ready for P11
```

For simple-dictionary fast-path, unchecked boxes are marked `[-]` (skipped by fast-path):
```
PHASE GATE CHECK — {ObjectName} [SIMPLE-DICT]:
  [x] P1 DDL   [x] P2 Sample   [-] P3 Dist   [x] P4 Lookup
  [-] P5 JOIN  [-] P6 BizLogic [-] P7 Views  [x] P8 SP-scan
  [-] P9 SP-logic [-] P9B ETL  [-] P10 Jira  [x] P10.5 Upstream
  → Ready for P11
```

**Phase 11 MUST refuse to generate if any `[ ]` (unchecked, non-skipped) box remains.**

## Hard Enforcement Reminders

- **⛔ ONE BATCH PER SESSION**: After end-of-batch banner → STOP. Do NOT start the next batch. New session required.
- **⛔ TIER SUFFIX ON EVERY DESCRIPTION (Rule 19)**: Every column description MUST end with `(Tier N — source.table)`. This suffix is written verbatim to Unity Catalog by Phase 11W. No exceptions.
- **⛔ LINEAGE BEFORE DOCS**: Write `.lineage.md` BEFORE `.md`. Phase 11 READS the lineage file to assign tiers. See `GATE-lineage-contract.mdc`.
- **⛔ TWO VALIDATIONS**: After each wiki doc, run BOTH `validate-wiki.ps1` (structural) AND `validate-tier1-coverage.ps1` (semantic). Both must pass before proceeding.
- **⛔ PHASE 9 IS HARD**: Read the SP code. Trace column assignments to source tables. The SP tells you WHERE each column comes from — you don't need to guess. If Phase 9 is skipped, Phase 13 lineage will be wrong, Phase 11 tiers will be wrong, and the semantic validation will fail.
